overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a detailed specification and Statement of Work. The agent conducted
  a comprehensive analysis of the existing codebase, identifying several
  critical missing features. Subsequently, the agent proceeded to implement
  these features. Key additions included a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness,
  complete with safety messaging, and the detection and reporting of specific
  sleep disorders like COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, each with tailored recommendations. Furthermore,
  a new section for external resources and links was integrated into both the
  web and PDF versions of the patient report. The implementation followed a
  structured approach, addressing each identified gap systematically.
